Gentle Annie
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:A name given to various hills or slopes (some, ironically, steep) on bridle-tracks and coach-roads and remaining as local names (occas. and locally, a creek): origin possibly in a popular song, transferred thence to slopes.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
