Date:  0/0/1988
Source:  Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author:  McGILL
Vol / Page:  48
Edition:
Quote:  Gentle Annie an easy slope or a difficult slope; originally a coachman's term. - a barmaid, specifically Annie Bowling in Queenstown area; ref. James McNeish's  Tavern in the Town; also the name of a song and a Turkish gun at the Dardanelles, 1915. [Check McNeish]
Notes:

